com.github.kaktushose.jda.commands.api

Interface Provider


  • public interface Provider
    An interface used to define a Provider of dependencies.

    In order to use the dependency injection feature of this framework at least one Provider class is needed. An instance of all Provider classes must be passed to JDACommandsBuilder.addProvider(Provider).

    A Provider class is a class that contains methods that are annotated with Produces and thus making objects available for dependency injection. All provided dependencies will be injected into fields annotated with Inject. This does only work for classes annotated with CommandController.

    Please note that this is only a very basic implementation of dependency injection and should only be used inside command classes.

    1.0.0
    Version:
